---
const projects = [
  {
    name: 'ezmode-games/ctd',
    description:
      'A crash reporter for modded games that helps players share crash context with mod creators. Built with modern tools and hosted on 90-days. Create a creator account and see when your mods are causing issues for your players. Self-hostable.',
    tags: ['rust', 'typescript', 'openapi'],
  },
  {
    name: 'ezmode-games/website',
    description:
      'This website. Built with Astro, React, and Tailwind CSS. Fully tested, linted, and documented. Because we practice what we preach.',
    tags: ['astro', 'react', 'tailwind'],
  },
];
---

<section id="about" class="w-full bg-ez-grey-800">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl grid grid-flow-col gap-4 md:gap-8 my-8 md:my-10 lg:my-16 p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">
        <div class="col-span-1">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-white sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl">
                Building tools for <span class="text-ez-yellow-500">gamers</span>, by gamers
            </h2>
            
            <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
                <p>
                    We're a small team of engineers and gamers, or is it gamers that make a living as engineers? Either way, we are getting tired of how modders are treated. 
                    So we decided to build things differently.
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    Our mission is simple: create tools that enhance gaming and modding without the predatory monetization, 
                    shady data practices, or toxic corporate culture that plagues most of gaming. Creators deserve better. Players deserve better.
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    We build open source; we do transparent. We're not here to get rich quick or sell your data. We're here to make gaming better for everyone.
                </p>
                
                <p class="font-semibold text-muted-foreground">
                    Sound good? Stick around. We're just getting started.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
            <h2 class="font-ui text-3xl font-bold text-ez-yellow-500 sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl">
                open source
            </h2>
           
            <div class="mt-12 space-y-8">
                {projects.map((project) => (
                    <div class="border-2 border-ez-grey-700 bg-ez-grey-900 p-4 transition-colors hover:border-ez-yellow-500 sm:p-6 md:p-8">
                        <div class="break-all font-mono text-lg font-bold text-white sm:text-xl md:text-2xl">
                            /{project.name}
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="mt-2 flex gap-2">
                            {project.tags.map((tag) => (
                                <span class="font-mono text-xs text-ez-grey-500">{tag}</span>
                            ))}
                        </div>
                        
                        <p class="mt-4 font-mono text-sm text-ez-grey-300 sm:text-base">
                            {project.description}
                        </p>
                        
                        <div class="mt-6">
                            <a 
                                href={`https://github.com/${project.name}`}
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="inline-block border-2 border-ez-yellow-500 bg-transparent px-4 py-2 font-ui text-sm font-bold text-ez-yellow-500 transition-colors hover:bg-ez-yellow-500 hover:text-ez-grey-900 sm:px-6 sm:py-3 sm:text-base"
                            >
                                VIEW ON GITHUB
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                ))}
            </div>    
        </div>
    </div>
</section>